</p>
<p class='vspace'>A sample startup script <em>start_molekel.sh</em> is provided.
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><h3>Launch from command line</h3>
<p>Modify <em>start_molekel.sh.sample</em> to add <em><code>&lt;molekel home directory&gt;/lib</code></em> to <code>LD_LIBRARY_PATH</code> and
enter the full path of Molekel's executable: <em><code>&lt;molekel home directory&gt;/bin/Molekel</code></em>.
</p>
<p class='vspace'>No need to cd to Molekel's home dir, the <em><code>cd ...</code></em> line can be commented.
</p>
</div>
        <div class='difftype'>to:</div>
        <div class='diffadd'><p>Uncompress the archive and add the <em>@molekel/lib@</em> directory to <code>LD_LIBRARY_PATH</code> then run <em><code>&lt;molekel root&gt;/bin/Molekel</code></em>:
</p>
<p class='vspace'>sh:
<code class='escaped'> export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=&lt;molekel installation dir&gt;/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH </code>
</p>
<p class='vspace'>csh:
<code class='escaped'> setenv LD_LIBRARY_PATH &lt;molekel installation dir&gt;/lib:${LD_LIBRARY_PATH} </code>
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div>
</div>
        <div class='difftype'>Changed lines 23-25 from:</div>
